reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth every penny. Ten out of ten.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this toy for my 18 month old great-grandson for Christmas, because he is obsessed with looking up in the sky and pointing at airplanes. The whole family was impressed with the quality of this toy, and it was nicer than I ever expected. His mother had it put together within 30 seconds. She said “I’m so thankful to the manufacturer for how easy this was“. I wish you could see his reaction and how excited he was. The joy on his face and the excitement in his voice was priceless! I’m getting ready to order another one for a different great-grandson for his birthday.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very cute and fun
reviews.reviewText: Update: Excellent customer service. Sent a new plane that’s working great and not broken at all. Overall, I recommend this product. My son loves it! And with the great customer service you will be happy.This item came cracked and missing parts, but actually still worked and was very fun and cute for my toddler. More pieces kept breaking as he played with it the first day we got it. Such a shame because it is a fun toy, but terrible quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Loud but with 10 min you can solve that problem
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. These are great toys the price… they are just very loud. Sadly you can’t have the lights without the music… or so I thought. One small screw driver, a pair of wire cutters, and 10 minutes of you time will give you the reward of a silent plane that still has the flashing lights. Take off the top, find the two green wires, give them a snip, put the top back on and BOOM no more sound. You could take the out batteries but where’s the fun in that? The lights are pretty cool and not as insanity inducing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars love or hate
reviews.reviewText: this is a toy you either love or hate! i got it for my son for christmas and he loves planes. the assembly was easy, but the wings fall out soooo easily! every time he would make it fly in the air, but pieces would come apart. needless to say he’s already lost almost every piece

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of my 2 year olds favorite gifts!
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my son for Christmas (he loves all things with an engine pretty much) and this is his top favorite gifts!! Even cuter in person, lights are bright, great bump n go action with noises. Feels light weight but has proven pretty durable thus far .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cute but noisy
reviews.reviewText: The airplanes are so cute and well made but they are too noisy. The sound the make when you turn them on is overwhelming and somewhat obnoxious. The sing-song, repetitive "music/airplane" sounds are very loud. There is no volume control. Would rate them high if it wasn't for the noise.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My kids love these!
reviews.reviewText: They are very durable! Have a great windup and go super fast! It does play music that you have to turn on and off from a switch! After a while the adults want to tear the batteries out! But the kids love them! We have gifted these as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A fun toy
reviews.reviewText: We were all surprised when we added the batteries to this airplane on Christmas morning. The bright lights and music brought a smile to everyone. It’s a fun toy that will be enjoyed for a long time…well made and colorful.
